BLOEFONTEIN Celtic have provided an update on their case against Mamelodi Sundowns. Celtic have protested the ineligibility of Sundowns defender Tebogo Langerman to take part in the Nedbank Cup final last weekend. Langerman picked up five yellow cards prior to the final and the experienced player was suspended for the match which was played at Orlando Stadium in Soweto. Sundowns won the match 1-0 to clinch the Nedbank Cup trophy. Celtic have now announced that the hearing date. "Our arbitration against Mamelodi Sundowns will be heard on Friday, 25 September 2020," the club said in a statement. ??????Club Statement??#LoveSiwelele????? pic.twitter.com/hG5kotPqtA 